OL,3,C'A ridiculous situation': Council
OL,4,Ccriticised for painting over potholes
OL,6,F"Our highways team work hard to
OL,7,Fcarefully coordinate and deliver
OL,8,Fhundreds of repairs every day, and we
OL,9,Frecognise that, ideally, the relining
OL,10,Fshould have been paused to allow the
OL,11,Frepair to be completed first.
OL,13,F"However, re-painting fading road
OL,14,Fmarkings is important to reduce risks
OL,15,Foutside schools, so the crew proceeded
OL,16,Fas planned.
OL,18,F"The pothole was repaired shortly
OL,19,Fafterwards, and the relining in that
OL,20,Fsection will follow shortly."
